ce:section.ce:para:
Cytotoxicity test of the synthesized BS-CDs was performed with the MTT assay method using L929 cells (Fig. 10
                        ). The L929 cells were cultured in fresh Dulbecco's Modified Eagle's Medium (DMEM) containing 10 % Fetal Bovine Serum (FBS) at 37 °C with 5 % CO2, seeded at 5000 cells per well in 96-well plates and incubator for 24 h. The BS-CDs were prepared with different concentrations (0, 5, 25, 50, 75, and 100 μL) from the stack solution (0.25 mg/mL in phosphate-buffered saline) to analyze its cell viability and compatibility. The optical density was recorded at 570 nm in the Elisa plate reader. As shown in Fig. S5, the BS-CDs have a mild toxic effect on the L929 cells after incubation and attain maximum cell viability of 68 to 85 % with respect to increasing the concentrations of BS-CDs (Fig. 11
                        ). The low cytotoxicity confirms the suitability of the fluorescent BS-CDs for bioimaging applications.
